[1] Nebraska
Date: Thu 31 Jan 2019
Source: KLIN News Talk, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.klin.com/2019/01/31/fourth-case-of-polio-like-illness-confirmed-in-nebraska-child/


Nebraska state health officials say a 4th case of a rare, polio-like illness has been confirmed in the state. The Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services said in a news release [Wed 30 Jan 2019] that the case of acute flaccid myelitis, or AFM, has been confirmed in a child in northeastern Nebraska. No other information about the child has been released.

The state's 1st case was reported in November [2018]. AFM can cause paralysis in the arms and legs and affects mainly children.

An increase in cases nationwide started in 2014. The department says from August 2014 through October 2018, there have been 527 confirmed cases of AFM in the US.

[Byline: Jane Monnich]

